    {\displaystyle Tf=Kf,Sg=Kg}
  which we can recognize as eigenvalue problems for the operators for 
  
    
      
        T
      
    
    {\displaystyle T}
   and 
  
    
      
        S
      
    
    {\displaystyle S}
  . If 
  
    
      
        T
      
    
    {\displaystyle T}
   is a compact, self-adjoint operator on the space 
  
    
      
        
          L
          
            2
          
        
        [
        0
        ,
        l
        ]
      
    
    {\displaystyle L^{2}[0,l]}
   along with the relevant boundary conditions, then by the Spectral theorem there exists a basis for 
  
    
      
        
          L
          
            2
          
        
        [
        0
        ,
