    {\displaystyle t}
   is square-integrable with respect to 
  
    
      
        x
      
    
    {\displaystyle x}
  , we can write this function as a linear combination of the 
  
    
      
        
          f
          
            λ
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle f_{\lambda }}
  . In particular, we know the solution 
  
    
      
        u
      
    
    {\displaystyle u}
   can be written as

  
    
      
        u
        (
        x
        ,
        t
        )
        =
        
          ∑
          
            λ
            ∈
